  "text": "Although no molecular data are available for B. laevis, B. melis or B.devosi; mitochondrial and nuclear genes of B. columnaris and B. potosis have recently been characterized and their phylogenetic relationship with other Baylisascaris species has been examined. The first phylogenetic analysis of B. columnaris from pet skunks in Europe showed closer affinity to B. procyonis compared to B. transfuga [CITATION_1] ) based on mitochondrial cytochrome c oxidase 1 and 2 (CO1 and CO2), ribosomal ITS1-5.8S-ITS2 and ribosomal 28S genes. This result was expected because B. columnaris was previously shown to be very similar to B. procyonis based on partial mitochondrial CO2 gene sequences (Danguodobiyam et al., 2009) . Phylogenetic analyses of the mitochondrial CO1 and ITS2 rDNA gene sequences showed that B. potosis had high genetic similarity to B. procyonis and B. columnaris [CITATION_2] .",
